section#sec-p-div-gps
    title #[m p]-divisible groups (Sachi)



    p
        | Why study  #[m p]-divisible groups (Jacob Stix).
        ol
            li
                | Analyse local #[m p]-adic galois action on #[m p]-torsion of elliptic curves, Serre's open image theorem.
                me \phi_l \colon G_K \to \Aut \lb l \rb
                | Surjective for almost all #[m l].
            li
                | Tool for representing #[m p]-adic cohomology, e.g #[m p]-adic hodge theory.
            li
                | Describe local properties of moduli spaces of abelian varieties which map to moduli spaces of #[m p]-divisible groups which can be described by semilinear algebra (Serre-Tate).
            li
                | Explicit local CFT via Lubin-Tate formal groups describing wildly ramified abelian extensions.
            li
                | The true fundamental group in characteristic #[m p] must include infinitesimal group schemes, #[m p]-divisible groups enter through their tate modules.
