        definition
            statement: p
                | Let #[m p] be a prime and #[m h] a non-negative integer.
                | A #[m p]-divisible group of height #[m h] is an inductive system
                me (G_v, i_v)
                | where each #[m G_v] is a group scheme #[m /R] of size #[m p^{vh}]
                me i_v \colon G_v \to G_{v+1}
                | identifies #[m G_v] with kernel of multiplication by #[m p^v].
                me 0 \to G_v \xrightarrow{i_v} G_{v+1} \xrightarrow{[p^v]} G_{v+1}
        remark
